fields.description:
*Assessment*

Using [s3cmd|https://github.com/s3tools/s3cmd] (version 1.5.0-rc1), uploading an 811M file
{code}
[root@odc-f-13 ~]# du -sh utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.raw
811M	utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.raw
[root@odc-f-13 ~]# qemu-img info utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.raw
image: utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.raw
file format: raw
virtual size: 17G (18467520512 bytes)
disk size: 810M
{code}
 caused the following error:
{code}
utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.raw -> s3://ubuntu-images/utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.raw  [part 1170 of 1175, 15MB]
 15728640 of 15728640   100% in    0s    31.88 MB/s  done
utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.raw -> s3://ubuntu-images/utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.raw  [part 1171 of 1175, 15MB]
 15728640 of 15728640   100% in    0s    29.05 MB/s  done
utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.raw -> s3://ubuntu-images/utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.raw  [part 1172 of 1175, 15MB]
 15728640 of 15728640   100% in    0s    32.78 MB/s  done
utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.raw -> s3://ubuntu-images/utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.raw  [part 1173 of 1175, 15MB]
 15728640 of 15728640   100% in    0s    29.56 MB/s  done
utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.raw -> s3://ubuntu-images/utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.raw  [part 1174 of 1175, 15MB]
 15728640 of 15728640   100% in    0s    32.18 MB/s  done
utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.raw -> s3://ubuntu-images/utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.raw  [part 1175 of 1175, 2048kB]
 2097152 of 2097152   100% in    0s     3.43 MB/s  done
WARNING: Retrying failed request: /utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.raw?uploadId=YBG6AFRTDBJMP3FOFNU8N11DLRWWAZESA0KWE9ZZBFMIXV7347R3FOYTVQW4UCGF
WARNING: 500 (InternalError): We encountered an internal error. Please try again.
WARNING: Waiting 3 sec...
WARNING: Retrying failed request: /utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.raw?uploadId=YBG6AFRTDBJMP3FOFNU8N11DLRWWAZESA0KWE9ZZBFMIXV7347R3FOYTVQW4UCGF
WARNING: 500 (InternalError): We encountered an internal error. Please try again.
WARNING: Waiting 6 sec...
WARNING: Retrying failed request: /utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.raw?uploadId=YBG6AFRTDBJMP3FOFNU8N11DLRWWAZESA0KWE9ZZBFMIXV7347R3FOYTVQW4UCGF
WARNING: 500 (InternalError): We encountered an internal error. Please try again.
WARNING: Waiting 9 sec...
WARNING: Retrying failed request: /utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.raw?uploadId=YBG6AFRTDBJMP3FOFNU8N11DLRWWAZESA0KWE9ZZBFMIXV7347R3FOYTVQW4UCGF

WARNING: Waiting 12 sec...
WARNING: Retrying failed request: /utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.raw?uploadId=YBG6AFRTDBJMP3FOFNU8N11DLRWWAZESA0KWE9ZZBFMIXV7347R3FOYTVQW4UCGF
WARNING: 500 (InternalError): We encountered an internal error. Please try again.
WARNING: Waiting 15 sec...
ERROR: S3 error: 500 (InternalError): We encountered an internal error. Please try again.
{code}

*Details*

The goal was to upload a 811M image using the --acl-public option with s3cmd.  The command was executed as follows:
{code}
[root@odc-f-13 ~]# ./s3cmd/s3cmd --config=.s3cfg-acct1-user01 put --acl-public utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.raw s3://ubuntu-images/utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.raw
WARNING: Module python-magic is not available. Guessing MIME types based on file extensions.
utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.raw -> s3://ubuntu-images/utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.raw  [part 1 of 1175, 15MB]
 15728640 of 15728640   100% in    0s    25.78 MB/s  done
utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.raw -> s3://ubuntu-images/utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.raw  [part 2 of 1175, 15MB]
 15728640 of 15728640   100% in    0s    33.39 MB/s  done
utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.raw -> s3://ubuntu-images/utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.raw  [part 3 of 1175, 15MB]
....
{code}
After the error happened, all services reported READY:
{code}
[root@odc-f-13 ~]# euca-describe-services | grep object
SERVICE	objectstorage     	SheHatesMe	SheHatesMe.objectstorage	ENABLED 	28  	http://10.104.10.11:8773/services/objectstorage	arn:euca:bootstrap:SheHatesMe:objectstorage:SheHatesMe.objectstorage/
SERVICE	objectstorage     	ShoesForRunning	ShoesForRunning.objectstorage	ENABLED 	28  	http://10.104.1.218:8773/services/objectstorage	arn:euca:bootstrap:ShoesForRunning:objectstorage:ShoesForRunning.objectstorage/
[root@odc-f-13 ~]# euca-describe-services | grep walrus
SERVICE	walrusbackend     	walrus    	Lines                	ENABLED 	28  	http://10.104.10.11:8773/services/WalrusBackend	arn:euca:bootstrap:walrus:walrusbackend:Lines/
{code}
However, if s3cmd was used to list the bucket contents s3://ubuntu-images, nothing showed up:
{code}
[root@odc-f-13 ~]# ./s3cmd/s3cmd --config=.s3cfg-acct1-user01 ls s3://ubuntu-images
[root@odc-f-13 ~]#
{code}
The command however worked for other buckets:
{code}
[root@odc-f-13 ~]# ./s3cmd/s3cmd --config=.s3cfg-acct1-user01 ls s3://testing-s3cmd
2014-09-04 23:44     18587   s3://testing-s3cmd/install.log

[root@odc-f-13 ~]# ./s3cmd/s3cmd --config=.s3cfg-acct1-user01 put --acl-public install.log.syslog s3://testing-s3cmd/install.log.syslog
WARNING: Module python-magic is not available. Guessing MIME types based on file extensions.
install.log.syslog -> s3://testing-s3cmd/install.log.syslog  [1 of 1]
 6595 of 6595   100% in    2s     2.45 kB/s  done
Public URL of the object is: http://testing-s3cmd.objectstorage.acme.eucalyptus-systems.com:8773/install.log.syslog

[root@odc-f-13 ~]# ./s3cmd/s3cmd --config=.s3cfg-acct1-user01 ls
2014-08-28 21:35  s3://coreos-production-ami
2014-07-28 04:50  s3://coreos-production-hvm-ami
2014-06-06 04:26  s3://fedora20-x86_64-hvm
2014-05-28 04:52  s3://precise-server-hvm
2014-06-02 15:06  s3://saucy-server-hvm
2014-06-10 00:45  s3://saucy-server-imported-20140609
2014-09-04 23:34  s3://testing-s3cmd
2014-06-15 22:37  s3://trusty-server-crypted
2014-06-03 12:31  s3://trusty-server-hvm-21040603
2014-06-17 17:43  s3://trusty-server-imported-20140617
2014-09-04 23:46  s3://ubuntu-images
2014-07-16 20:28  s3://ubuntu-precise-x86_64-9g-hvm
2014-07-21 20:11  s3://ubuntu-trusty-server-google-auth-x86_64-hvm
2014-07-22 19:05  s3://ubuntu-utopic-server-x86_64-18G
2014-06-05 02:23  s3://utopic-8g-server-hvm
2014-06-02 14:34  s3://utopic-server-5g-paravirt
2014-06-02 14:54  s3://utopic-server-8g-paravirt
2014-05-28 00:10  s3://utopic-server-hvm
2014-06-17 17:07  s3://vmware-centos6.5-imported
2014-06-18 04:12  s3://vmware-centos6.5-imported-disk2
2014-06-18 04:34  s3://vmware-centos6.5-imported-disk3
{code}

*Steps*

# Set up Eucalyptus 4.0.1 cloud with Eucalyptus DNS, Cloudformation, Load Balancer services enabled
# Download s3cmd from github (https://github.com/s3tools/s3cmd)
# Set up an s3cfg file.  For example:
{code}
[default]
access_key = AKI6GWITDEHGJIEBTREA
access_token =
add_encoding_exts =
add_headers =
bucket_location = US
cache_file =
cloudfront_host = cloudfront.amazonaws.com
default_mime_type = binary/octet-stream
delay_updates = False
delete_after = False
delete_after_fetch = False
delete_removed = False
dry_run = False
enable_multipart = True
encoding = UTF-8
encrypt = False
follow_symlinks = False
force = False
get_continue = False
gpg_command = /usr/local/bin/gpg
gpg_decrypt = %(gpg_command)s -d --verbose --no-use-agent --batch --yes --passphrase-fd %(passphrase_fd)s -o %(output_file)s %(input_file)s
gpg_encrypt = %(gpg_command)s -c --verbose --no-use-agent --batch --yes --passphrase-fd %(passphrase_fd)s -o %(output_file)s %(input_file)s
gpg_passphrase = 22dark10man
guess_mime_type = True
host_base = objectstorage.acme.eucalyptus-systems.com:8773
host_bucket = %(bucket)s.objectstorage.acme.eucalyptus-systems.com:8773
human_readable_sizes = False
invalidate_default_index_on_cf = False
invalidate_default_index_root_on_cf = True
invalidate_on_cf = False
list_md5 = False
log_target_prefix =
mime_type =
multipart_chunk_size_mb = 15
preserve_attrs = True
progress_meter = True
proxy_host =
proxy_port = 0
recursive = False
recv_chunk = 4096
reduced_redundancy = False
secret_key = X6iF2kYYZ4jQxfO8p5Zsgb7j4G6aVF8CluvAdj6G
send_chunk = 4096
service_path =
simpledb_host = sdb.amazonaws.com
skip_existing = False
socket_timeout = 300
urlencoding_mode = normal
use_https = False
verbosity = WARNING
website_endpoint = http://%(bucket)s.s3-website-%(location)s.amazonaws.com/
website_error =
website_index = index.html
{code}
# Download Ubuntu Cloud image - http://cloud-images.ubuntu.com/utopic/current/utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.img
# Convert to raw image using qemu-img:
{code}
qemu-img convert -O raw utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.img utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.raw
{code}
# Use qemu-img to increase the size of the image from 2.2G to 17G:
{code}
qemu-img resize utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.raw +15G
{code}
# Create a bucket using s3cmd:
{code}
./s3cmd/s3cmd --config=.s3cfg-acct1-user01 mb s3://ubuntu-images
{code}
# Upload image to bucket
{code}
./s3cmd/s3cmd --config=.s3cfg-acct1-user01 put --acl-public utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.raw s3://ubuntu-images/utopic-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.raw
{code}

[~zhill], would you please confirm the config and or use case of this issue.

This looks like an issue with the 'CompleteMultipartUpload' API call from s3cmd. It looks like the parts were uploaded successfully but the commit is failing for some reason. s3cmd uses MPU for larger file uploads automatically unless you disable it. 

This should work, and the s3cmd config looks good. If the parts are successful then the upload should be able to be completed. The testcase for this issue is a MPU with >1000 parts (this specific image created 1175 parts). 

This is a bug. I will assign it. We should target it for 4.0.2 as this will be customer affecting for some tools.
